reviewText: I watched this online. What a powerful part of history not known to most people. But after watching Black Panther, I seek out true stories of African royalty, persistence and revolts. This fits all 3. Queen Nanny taught her people to resist and insist. The Brits could not take over her country and enslave her people. She saw to that. 25 Maroons defeated 500 British Troops! Eventually, the Brits had to admit defeat and actually "work" with the Maroon people. What a concept.
Excellent documentary about a little-known but powerful woman who took on the mighty British army and a very engaging part of Jamaica's history
i love it i love it. im glad i bought this! ^___^
